## File 3 of 6 — `backend/app/config.py`

**📚 Concept: Configuration classes and the why of dev vs production settings**

Your app behaves differently depending on where it's running. On your laptop you want detailed error messages. In production (real server with real users) you want those hidden — showing stack traces to users is a security risk. Config classes let you switch between these modes with one environment variable.
```
backend/app/
└── config.py